===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|head=[[screw]] [[thread]]}}
#{{engineering}} A [[helical]] [[ridge]] which [[wrap#Verb|wrap]]s around an [[elongated]] [[cylindre]], or a [[groove]] [[spiral#Verb|spiraling]] around the [[wall]] of a [[bore]], used to [[convert]] a [[rotation]]al [[movement]] into a [[linear]] one.
#*''An internal '''screw thread''' is cut with a "tap", while external '''screw threads''' are cut with a "die".''

